article.headline: Hampton 77, N. Carolina A&T 65
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Jeff Granger scored 21 points and Jaz Cowan had 14 points and 13 rebounds Monday night, leading Hampton past North Carolina A&T, 77-65. The Pirates (8-9, 6-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) led 44-32 at halftime and won by dominating the offensive glass. They had 18 of their 44 rebounds on the offensive end, and turned them into 27 points. The Aggies had 14 points on 12 offensive rebounds. Jason Wills led North Carolina A&T with 31 points and 11 rebounds. Bruce Brown added 12 points and Rashad West scored 10 for Hampton.
